text: Lenora is an unincorporated community in Fillmore County, in the U.S. state of Minnesota. ==History== Lenora was laid out in 1855. A post office was established at Lenora in 1856, and remained in operation until it was discontinued in 1905. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Fillmore County, Minnesota Category:Unincorporated communities in Minnesota
title: Lenora, Minnesota
